	<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading" lang="en">Language module</h1>
	
	<div id="bodyContent" class="mw-body-content">
		<div id="siteSub" class="noprint">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</div>
		<div id="contentSub"></div>
		
		
		
		<div id="jump-to-nav"></div>
		<a class="mw-jump-link" href="#mw-head">Jump to navigation</a>
		<a class="mw-jump-link" href="#p-search">Jump to search</a>
		<div id="mw-content-text" lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><div class="mw-parser-output"><div role="note" class="hatnote navigation-not-searchable">This article is about the structure in the <a href="/wiki/Human_brain" title="Human brain">human brain</a>. For the software design technique supported by some programming languages, see <a href="/wiki/Modular_programming" title="Modular programming">Modular programming</a>.</div>
